# Heartgarden — local run, preview, and restarts (`heartgarden/`)

Use this whenever the user (or task) involves **running heartgarden**, **restarting the dev server**, **previewing in the browser**, **`localhost`**, **Cursor Simple Browser**, or **testing the UI** against a local server.

## Commands (execute; do not only instruct)

- **Working directory:** **`heartgarden/`** (Next app root; see `heartgarden/docs/NAMING.md`).
- **Start or restart:** **`pnpm run dev`** (`next dev --webpack --port 3000`). Run it in the integrated terminal; wait until the server is listening.
- **URL:** **`http://localhost:3000`** or **`http://127.0.0.1:3000`**. Same host the dev banner prints; avoid starting a second `next dev` on the same folder/port.
- **Do not** recommend **`dev:preview`** or **`HEARTGARDEN_DEV_BOOT_NO_GATE`** — removed; default **`pnpm run dev`** is enough.

## Boot PIN gate (local only)

- In **`next dev`**, the boot PIN gate is **off by default** — no PIN or special env is required to enter the app at localhost.
- **Production** and **`next start`** are unchanged (real `HEARTGARDEN_BOOT_*` still apply when configured).
- To **test the PIN flow locally**, set **`HEARTGARDEN_DEV_ENFORCE_BOOT_GATE=1`** in **`heartgarden/.env.local`** and restart dev. Details: **`heartgarden/.env.local.example`**, **`heartgarden/AGENTS.md`** (Next.js dev paragraph).

